{"id":10979,"date":"2016-07-02T00:00:00","date_gmt":"2016-07-01T23:00:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/mirandanet.ac.uk\/book-reviews\/"},"modified":"2021-03-24T22:11:12","modified_gmt":"2021-03-24T22:11:12","slug":"book-reviews","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/mirandanet.ac.uk\/book-reviews\/","title":{"rendered":"Book Reviews"},"content":{"rendered":"<div>\n<hr style=\"border: 1px dotted #93152c;\">\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Book Reviews<\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<hr style=\"border: 1px dotted #93152c;\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/06\/RMrosette.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-7197\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-7197\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/06\/RMrosette.png\" alt=\"Rosette\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"><\/a><\/p>\n<div style=\"font-size: 13pt;\">\n<p>The Book Review section of the journal aims to include two broad areas of interest:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>reviews of published works by MirandaNet members.<\/li>\n<li>reviews of works by other authors that are of interest to the membership.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>While retaining the traditional title of &#8216;Book Reviews&#8217; the range of reviewed works may be considered quite broadly and is not confined to print titles.&nbsp; Where digital artefacts are reviewed they should be content oriented (i.e. they present an extended argument, discussion or account of an issue, topic or theme) and ideally accessible for the foreseeable future or at least can be referenced to an archive.<\/p>\n<p>Review of relevant television programmes, films, and lectures such as those available on <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ted.com\/talks\">Ted talks<\/a> would all form useful subjects for review.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center; margin-left: 30px; margin-right: 30px;\">MirandaNet members are invited to contribute reviews. Please email <a href=\"mailto:editor@mirandanet.ac.uk\">editor@mirandanet.ac.uk<\/a><\/p>\n<hr style=\"border: 1px dotted #9e152c;\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/06\/bookshelf.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-7275\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-7275 size-full\" style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0:;\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/06\/bookshelf.jpg\" alt=\"Bookshelf\" width=\"1015\" height=\"159\"><\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 12pt; overflow: auto;\">\n<hr style=\"border: 1px dotted #9e152c;\">\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-8560\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/06\/9781138195820.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\"><span style=\"color: #9e152c;\">Digital Technologies and Change in Education: The Arena Framework<\/span><br \/>\nNiki Davis.<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">2017. Routledge.&nbsp;<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em><a href=\" \/review-digital-technologies-change-education\/\">Review by Christina Preston<\/a>. Published: 15 Oct 2017.<\/em><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 12pt; overflow: auto;\">\n<hr style=\"border: 1px dotted #9e152c;\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; overflow: auto; color: #9e152c;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.co.uk\/Negotiating-Neoliberalism-Developing-Alternative-Educational\/dp\/9463008535\/ref=sr_1_1_twi_har_2?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1494770791&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=Negotiating+Neoliberalism\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-8560\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/06\/neoliberalcover.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\"><\/a>Negotiating Neoliberalism: Developing Alternative Educational Visions<\/span><br \/>\nTim Rudd and Ivor F. Goodson &nbsp;(eds)<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">2017. SensePublishers.&nbsp;<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em><a href=\" \/review-negotiating-neoliberalism\/\">Review by John Galloway<\/a>. 14 May 2017.<\/em><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 12pt; overflow: auto;\">\n<hr style=\"border: 1px dotted #9e152c;\">\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-8560\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/06\/making_a_difference-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"Making a difference cover\" width=\"100\"> <span style=\"color: #9e152c; vertical-align: baseline;\">Making a difference in Education: What the Evidence Says<\/span><br \/>\nRobert Cassen, Sandra McNally and Anna Vignoles.<br \/>\n2015.&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/www.routledge.com\/products\/9780415529228\">Routledge<\/a>.<br \/>\n<em><a href=\"\/mirandanet-journal\/book-reviews\/making-a-difference-in-education-what-the-evidence-says\/\">Review by Terry Freedman<\/a>, published: 19 Feb 2016.<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<hr style=\"border: 1px dotted #9e152c;\">\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-8560\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/06\/dig-lit-primary-teachers-210x300.jpg\" alt=\"dig-lit-primary-teachers\" width=\"70\" height=\"100\"> <span style=\"text-transform: uppercase; color: #9e152c;\">Digital Literacy for primary teachers<\/span><br \/>\nMoira Savage and Antony Barnett.<br \/>\n2015. <a href=\"http:\/\/criticalpublishing.com\/titles\/teacher-training\/digital-literacy-for-primary-teachers.html\">Critical Publishing Ltd<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"\/mirandanet-journal\/book-reviews\/digital-literacy-for-primary-teachers-moira-savage-and-antony-barnett\/\">Review by Christina Preston<\/a>, published: 13 Jul 2015.<\/p>\n<hr style=\"border: 1px dotted #9e152c;\">\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-5763\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/06\/narrative-ecologies-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"narrative ecologies\" width=\"67\" height=\"100\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; overflow: auto; text-transform: uppercase; color: #9e152c;\">Narrative Ecologies: Teachers as Pedagogical Toolmakers.<\/span><br \/>\nKeith Turvey<br \/>\n2015. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.routledge.com\/products\/9780415622431\">Routledge<\/a>.<br \/>\n<em><a href=\"\/mirandanet-journal\/book-reviews\/narrative-ecologies-teachers-as-pedagogical-toolmakers\/\">Review by Christina Preston<\/a>, published: 15 January 2015.<\/em><\/p>\n<hr style=\"border: 1px dotted #9e152c;\">\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-5755\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/06\/design-patterns-196x300.jpg\" alt=\"design patterns\" width=\"65\" height=\"100\"><span style=\"text-transform: uppercase; color: #9e152c;\">Practical Design Patterns for teaching and learing with technology<\/span><br \/>\nYishay Mor, Harvey Mellar, Steven Warburton and Niall Winters (Eds).<br \/>\n2014. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sensepublishers.com\/catalogs\/bookseries\/technology-enhanced-learning-1\/practical-design-patterns-for-teaching-and-learning-with-technology\/\">Sense Publishers<\/a>.<br \/>\n<em><a href=\"\/mirandanet-journal\/book-reviews\/practical-design-patterns-for-teaching-and-learning-with-technology\/\">Review by Christina Preston<\/a>, published: 15 January 2015.<\/em><\/p>\n<hr style=\"border: 1px dotted #9e152c;\">\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-5754\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/06\/ultimate-guide-198x300.jpg\" alt=\"ultimate guide\" width=\"66\" height=\"100\"><span style=\"text-transform: uppercase; color: #9e152c;\">The Ultimate Guide to Using ICT Across the Curriculum (For Primary Teachers): Web, widgets, whiteboards and beyond!<\/span><br \/>\nJon Audain.<br \/>\n2014. <a href=\"http:\/\/www.bloomsbury.com\/uk\/the-ultimate-guide-to-using-ict-across-the-curriculum-for-primary-teachers-9781441144003\/\">Bloomsbury<\/a>.<br \/>\n<em><a href=\"\/mirandanet-journal\/book-reviews\/the-ultimate-guide-to-using-ict-across-the-curriculum\/\">Review by Christina Preston<\/a>, published: 15 January 2015.<\/em>[\/cs_text]<div id=\"\" class=\"x-text\" style=\"\" ><hr style=\"border: 1px dotted #9e152c;\">\n<p><img lo